======================================May 22
	-	for loop
	-	while loop
			let number = prompt("Enter a number greater than 10:");

			while (number <= 10) {
			  number = prompt("Too small! Enter a number greater than 10:");
			}

			The condition number <= 10 is checked before running the loop body.

			If the user initially enters a valid number (e.g. 15) the loop is skipped entirely.

console.log("You entered:" number);
======================================May 23

	-	do while
			let number;

			do {
			  number = prompt("Enter a number greater than 10:");
			} while (number <= 10);

			console.log("You entered:" number);

			The loop runs at least once even if the condition is false on the first try.

			Useful when you want the code to execute at least once
